transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Biagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hello?

Speaker 1: Yeah, hello, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, just trying to cancel an order, a prescription that's been ongoing.

Speaker 1: Okay, what was your first and last name, please, sir?

Speaker 2: Fred Quart.

Speaker 1: Can you spell the last name for me, please?

Speaker 2: C-L-A-R-K.

Speaker 1: What's your zip code, Mr. Clark?

Speaker 2: 92084.

Speaker 1: Perfect.

Speaker 2: Are you 1046 Little Gopher Canyon Road?

Speaker 1: Correct.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Looks like you've been getting the pills, well, every two months, every 60 days for quite some time.

Speaker 1: I can pause that for you, Mr. Clark, if you just need more time, for up to six months at a time.

Speaker 1: I can push that next week forward all the way until July.

Speaker 2: I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: I'm just going to cancel it.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: I can do that for you, but I did want to let you know you are a VIP member with us,

Speaker 1: and we are the only ones who get that FDA-approved medicine from Pfizer.

Speaker 1: If I do cancel it, I won't be able to open the prescription back up for you in the future,

Speaker 1: so I just wanted to make sure you were aware.

Speaker 1: Before I did finalize that for you, you could have to get cheap pills from India, China,

Speaker 1: some of that will really mess you up.

Speaker 2: I'm aware.

Speaker 2: I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: Thank you very much.

Speaker 2: No worries, no worries.

Speaker 1: You are all set, Mr. Clark.

Speaker 1: I'm canceling that for you now, and it has been done.

Speaker 1: You won't get anything else.

Speaker 1: You won't be billed.

Speaker 1: You won't be sent any more medicine.

Speaker 1: You're all set.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye now.
